descriptions.value: Great street exposure for this large corner commercial space. Fully updated, the unit's contemporary design greets you as you enter the open floor plan space in this timeless Victorian building. Currently occupied by an award-winning architecture firm, this commercial office space offers great income with its Triple-Net lease of $9,300 / month. A separate area exists in the back and enjoys a kitchenette with dishwasher and sink, copy room, and full bathroom. An ADA-compliant half bath is also conveniently located in the main office space area. The unit enjoys an insane location with a Walk Score of 98, just steps to spectacular retail, restaurants, cafes, shops, and Alta Plaza Park.

2053 Fillmore is located on one of the most exclusive shopping blocks in San Francisco’s Pacific Heights neighborhood. The surrounding area has the highest average household income in all of San Francisco. The space is proximately located near the busy corner of Fillmore and California, with close proximity to park-ing and public transportation. This walkable tree-lined block is home to Rag and Bone, Space NK, James Perse, Noosh and many other well-known tenants. Features +/- 685 SF Elegant storefront with large display window Large signage block with potential for additional blade signage Excellent visibility from California and Fillmore Streets Move-in condition Nearby neighbors include Credo, Reformation, Goop, Gorjana, Jane, and many others.

Opportunity to Lease One of the Best Retail Spaces in San Francisco's Legendary and Busy Japantown.​ This Space Features Floor to Ceiling Glass on 3 Sides, Extraordinary Views of the Pagoda and Peace Plaza, and a Spacious Floor Plan.​ One of Three Remaining in the United States, Japantown Consists of About Six Square City Blocks in San Francisco.​ Japan Center East & West Are Located in the Heart of Japantown and Include Over 100,000 Square Feet of Shops and Restaurants.​ Japan Center Retail Sites Can Accommodate Both Large and Small Businesses, Ranging in Size From as Little as 300 to as Large as 15,000 Square Feet.​ Japan Center Represents Japanese Culture With One-of-a-kind Retailers and Restaurants.​ The Center is Welcome to All but Strives to Preserve a Culture That Deeply Contributes to San Francisco's History.​ The Property is Easily Accessible by Public Transportation, and Also Contains Ample Underground and Street Parking.​

descriptions.value: Rare opportunity to occupy a large footprint on San Francisco’s Upper Fillmore Street. 2261 Fillmore Street is located on one of the prestigious shopping blocks in San Francisco’s Pacific Heights neighborhood. Frame, Reformation, Veronica Beard, Gorjana, and Rag & Bone are just some of the hot shops dotting the district. Upper Fillmore is also home to some of San Francisco’s best restaurants such as SPQR, Woodhouse Fish Co., and Noosh. The space features massive ceilings, rear loading, and incredibly visibility on one of San Francisco’s best shopping streets. Theater uses encouraged, but landlord open to a variety of uses. Features +/- 4,662 SF + 1,013 SF Mezzanine Located in the heart of San Franciscos prestigious Upper Fillmore District Vast ceilings Rear exiting & loading possible Landlord supportive of all theater uses, but open to a variety of other uses as well.
